2. About the Lifegrid	144.6999969482422	390.7367248535156	12.0	116.08799743652344	30
The LG is a tool used to construct a visual chronological framework of a person's	144.6999969482422	419.47967529296875	11.0	394.4052276611328	31
life (RICHARDSON, ONG, SIM & CORBETT, 2009; WILSON et al., 2007). It	144.6999969482422	433.5796813964844	11.0	373.0209503173828	31
generally takes a chart-like structure with several rows and columns, where the	144.6999969482422	447.7796936035156	11.0	384.9340362548828	31
rows usually represent the person's life in years (each row is a particular year)	144.6999969482422	461.87969970703125	11.0	380.0060577392578	31
and the columns represent significant life events (WILSON et al., 2007). The	144.6999969482422	476.0796813964844	11.0	373.3400421142578	31
significant life events are selected aspects of the participants' lives that the	144.6999969482422	490.1796875	11.0	363.77012634277344	31
researcher wishes to explore. These aspects are closely related to the research	144.6999969482422	504.37969970703125	11.0	388.12416076660156	31
questions of the study and can include topics such as family life, friends and	144.6999969482422	518.4796752929688	11.0	370.8760528564453	31
social relationships, place of residence, occupation and so forth. For example, the	144.6999969482422	532.6796875	11.0	398.83827209472656	31
LG was used to explore the life course of cancer patients using selected aspects	144.6999969482422	546.7796630859375	11.0	392.7881622314453	31
such as "personal life events," "education, lifestyle," "residence," "occupation"	144.6999969482422	560.9796752929688	11.0	377.98219299316406	31
and "other" (NOVOGRADEC, 2009, p.2). A completed LG then allows the	144.6999969482422	575.0797119140625	11.000015258789062	358.8090362548828	31
researcher to assess how the participant's life has changed over a certain period	144.6999969482422	589.2797241210938	11.0	392.88722229003906	31
of time and when these changes occurred. When the LG is used to facilitate	144.6999969482422	603.3796997070312	11.0	370.7770538330078	31
qualitative data gathering, it further allows the researchers to unpack how the	144.6999969482422	617.5797119140625	11.0	376.37611389160156	31
participants experienced and managed these changes. [4]	144.6999969482422	631.6796875	11.0	283.54701232910156	31
The lifegrid tool was developed to address research concerns related to	144.6999969482422	659.979736328125	11.0	349.6681365966797	32
participant recall and validity in retrospective medical studies (BELL, 2005). It has	144.6999969482422	674.1796875	11.0	396.38514709472656	32
traditionally been used to collect quantitative data on the development of	144.6999969482422	688.2797241210938	11.0	353.0450897216797	32
illnesses, pain and health behaviors (BERNEY & BLANE, 1997; PARRY,	144.6999969482422	702.479736328125	11.0	353.5618133544922	32
